                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <button data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#receding-hairline" type="button">Receding
                            hairline</button>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <button data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#reduced-volume" type="button">Reduced
                            volume</button>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <button data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#weaker-strands" type="button">Weaker
                            strands</button>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <button data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#shedding" type="button">Shedding</button>
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="crown-thinning">
                        <p>For many women, the crown is one of the first areas to show thinning. Hormonal changes during
                            menopause, stress, and genetics can all shorten the natural growth cycle. </p>
                        <p>Over time, follicles in this area shrink and produce finer strands, which makes the scalp
                            more visible at the top or back of the head.</p>
                        <strong>How Q-Renew helps</strong>
                        <p>By delivering light energy deep into the scalp, Q-Renew supports follicle activity in the
                            crown area, helping to reduce visible thinning and improve overall coverage.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="widening-part-line">
                        <p>One of the most common and distressing signs of thinning is when the part line gets wider. It
                            happens as follicles along the central scalp miniaturize and produce thinner, weaker hairs.
                        </p>
                        <p>This gradual loss of density makes the scalp more noticeable through the part.</p>
                        <strong>How Q-Renew helps</strong>
                        <p>Q-Renew's lasers are precisely distributed across the scalp, targeting the central line where
                            thinning is most visible. By stimulating follicles along the part, it helps encourage
                            thicker strands and restore a more balanced, fuller-looking part line.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="receding-hairline">
                        <p>Thinning around the temples and hairline not only affects volume but can change the shape of
                            the face.</p>
                        <p>This area is particularly vulnerable to hormonal shifts, stress, and genetics, and the
                            delicate hairs here are often the first to weaken or stop growing.</p>
                        <strong>How Q-Renew helps</strong>
                        <p>Q-Renew provides full-front coverage, delivering light directly to the temples and hairline.
                            This helps support follicle activity in these sensitive zones, encouraging healthier growth
                            and helping to maintain your natural hairline for longer.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="reduced-volume">
                        <p>Hair that looks flat or limp is a sign that follicles are producing finer strands. Over time,
                            this reduction in density changes the overall body and fullness of hair, leaving it without
                            its natural lift and bounce.</p>
                        <strong>How Q-Renew helps</strong>
                        <p>By supporting follicle function across the entire scalp, Q-Renew encourages thicker, stronger
                            hairs to grow in. The result is healthier density, giving hair more lift, movement, and
                            natural fullness.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="weaker-strands">
                        <p>When follicles aren't functioning at their best, the hair they produce grows in finer and
                            more fragile. Weak strands break easily and don't grow as long, creating the sense that your
                            hair is stuck at a shorter length and never feels strong.</p>
                        <strong>How Q-Renew helps</strong>
                        <p>Q-Renew stimulates the follicle at the root, encouraging stronger hair fiber production over
                            time. With consistent use, strands can grow in thicker and more resilient, reducing breakage
                            and restoring a healthier look and feel.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tab-pane fade" id="shedding">
                        <p>Excessive daily shedding can feel like an ongoing battle, with hair collecting in the shower,
                            on your pillow, or in your brush.</p>
                        <p>Shedding often occurs when follicles exit the growth phase too early, a process influenced by
                            stress, hormones, or genetics.</p>
                        <strong>How Q-Renew helps</strong>
                        <p>Q-Renew works with your natural hair cycle, helping to extend the growth phase of follicles.
                            Many users first notice a reduction in excess shedding before seeing new density, which sets
                            the stage for stronger, fuller hair over time.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
